data.body:
Found a potential bug while checking the code for unused variables: https://github.com/godotengine/godot/blob/a7fc046/tools/editor/io_plugins/editor_mesh_import_plugin.cpp#L523-L524

```
if (generate_normals || force_smooth)
    surf_tool->generate_normals();
if (uvs.size() && (normals.size() || generate_normals))
    surf_tool->generate_tangents();
```

Copy-paste mistake in the second `if`? I guess it should check `generate_tangents` (currently unused, which is how I found out about this) and not `generate_normals`). The fix is trivial but since I have no experience with meshes I'd like a confirmation :)

But this still leave differences when using the function on nodes and resources, because it'll show two extra properties: `"script/script"` and `"__meta__"`. IMO those two properties should be removed from the list, since both properties exists on every `Object` and can be accessed from script, for example:

``` GDScript
    var script = object.get("script/script")
    # or
    var script = object.get_script()

    var meta = object.get("__meta__")
    # or
    var meta = {}
    for name in object.get_meta_list():
        meta[name] = object.get_meta(name)
```

And the return value of the function will be "clean" since it'll exclude object internal variables.

Closes #5566.
